data.title: Outsourcing - 3rd Party Resources and Expertise for hire - OPM, Tax, Incorporate, Legal, Writing, Development
data.meta_description: Advertisers with Affiliate Program: Outsource your Program Management. Internet Marketers: You can't do everything yourself, especially as a small business. You should outsource certain things and or get help from an expert 3rd party.
data.text:
LogoDescription eLance.com find the experts you need to get the job done. online services marketplace. Find designers, programmers, writers, accountants and other professionals.

RentACoder.com - How software gets done. Outsource a programming project, rent a coder.

iFreelance.com - Need Freelance Professionals? Free Freelance Services Marketplace.

AllFreeLanceWork.com freelance jobboard, freelance community, small business article base, & home business information zone.

ScriptLance.com - Find a freelance programmer for your Web Development project

GetAFreelancer.com - find a Freelancer or offer your services to others.

Sologig.com is the nation's leading freelance resource and home to a large number of projects

Kasamba.com - Live Expert Advice, Coaching and Professional Counseling, Computers & Programming, Tutoring, Business & Finance, including Tax, eCommerce and Marketing & Advertising, Legal and more.

SitePoint Marketplace - is a great marketplace to find skilled programmers, designers, copy editors and writers for relatively low cost. You are dealing with the freelancers in a contest like setting, where you specify the price and then receive submissings until the listing expires.

oDesk - is another great marketplace, similar to eLance to find quality developers and designers for your development and graphic design needs. oDesk also comes with a whole set of collaboration tools for the use during the actual project implementation phase, which is a nice bonus, if you don't have anything like that in place already (e.g. Basecamp). FreeLanceSwitch - is a blog about outsourcing and freelancing with forums and a marketplace attached to it. You will not only find professional help there, but resources and tips for how to go about outsourcing projects as well. DirectFreeLance - is another freelance job board/marketplace to hire some outside help on a per project/limited time basis. GetACoder - is another marketplace to find a programmer/coder for your small development projects needs. Drupal Groups (Developers) - seemingly an odd place to look for some freelance workers to hire, unless you need help with customizing your Drupal open source content managment system, but the members who are hanging out in those groups are usually knowledgeable beyond just the Drupal platform and willing to work on other projects for you as well. 99 Designs - is highly recommended for custom design and logo works at an unbeatable price for premium quality results.
